The paper discusses a method for performing sensitivity analysis on Bayesian networks, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The method presented aims to reduce the computational cost of the analysis, which is a common concern in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves using a junction tree for propagation, which is a technique commonly used in probabilistic graphical models and inference (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the extension of the method to n-way sensitivity analysis, which involves studying sets of parameters, a topic related to statistical inference (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
